The paper deals with a deployment problem of a robotic swarm, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The problem involves decision-making under uncertainty, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The use of Markov Decision Processes (MDPs) and control strategies indicates the involvement of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also proposes efficient solution algorithms, which suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.MA) and optimization (cs.LG) techniques.
